olive oil
1 punnet cherry tomatoes
½ tin sweetcorn
2 clove garlic
1 packet ciabatta
30 g butter
1 packet Diced Chicken
1 bag salad leaves
1 drizzle white wine vinegar
1 packet Dill & Parsley Mayonnaise
1 sachet Louisiana spice blend

• Halve cherry tomatoes. Drain sweetcorn (see ingredients). Finely chop garlic. Cut or tear ciabatta into bite-sized chunks.

• In a large frying pan, heat a generous drizzle of olive oil over a medium-high heat.
• Cook ciabatta until golden and slightly crisp, 5-6 minutes.
• Add the butter and garlic and cook, tossing, until fragrant, 1 minute. Season with salt and pepper, then transfer to a large bowl.

• Return the frying pan to a high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. When oil is hot, cook diced chicken, sweetcorn and Louisiana spice blend, tossing occasionally, until browned and cooked through, 5-6 minutes. Set aside.
• Meanwhile, add mixed salad leaves, cherry tomatoes and a drizzle of white wine vinegar and olive oil to the bowl with croutons. Season to taste.

• Divide crouton salad between bowls.
• Top with Louisiana chicken and corn.
• Spoon over dill & parsley mayonnaise to serve.